{{Sexagenary cycle comprehensive}}
'''Teichuu''' (丁丑) (ひのとうし、ていかのうし、ていちゅう) is one of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|干支}}.

It is the 14th combination in the Sexagenary cycle; the preceding combination is {{ill|Bingzi|ja|丙子}} and the following combination is {{ill|Wuyin|ja|戊寅}}. In the system of {{ill|Yin-Yang and the Five Elements|ja|陰陽五行思想|lt=Yin-Yang Five Elements|lt_ja=陰陽五行}}, the {{ill|Ten Heavenly Stems|ja|十干}}’ {{ill|Ding|ja|丁}} represents yin {{ill|Fire|ja|火}}, while the {{ill|Twelve Earthly Branches|ja|十二支}}’ {{ill|Ox|ja|丑}} represents yin {{ill|Earth|ja|土}}, and they interact by {{ill|Mutual Generation|ja|五行思想#相生（そうじょう）|lt=Mutual Generation|lt_ja=相生}} (Fire generates Earth).

== Years of Teichuu ==
A year in the {{ill|Common Era|ja|西暦}} that leaves a remainder of 17 when divided by 60 is a {{ill|Year|ja|年}} of Teichuu.
