'''Yin Fire Ox also known as  Teichuu''' (丁丑) (ひのとうし、ていかのうし、ていちゅう) is one of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|干支|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}.

It is the 14th combination in the Sexagenary cycle; the preceding combination is {{ill|Bingzi|ja|丙子|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} and the following combination is {{ill|Wuyin|ja|戊寅|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}. In the system of {{ill|Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|ja|陰陽五行思想|lt=Yin-Yang Five Elements|lt_ja=陰陽五行|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|lt=Ten Heavenly Stems|ja|十干|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}’ {{ill|Ding|ja|丁|1=Hinoto (丁)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} represents yin {{ill|Fire|ja|火|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}, while the {{ill|Twelve Earthly Branches|1=Earthly Branches|lt=Twelve Earthly Branches|ja|十二支|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}’ {{ill|Ox|ja|丑|1=Ox (zodiac)|lt=Ox (丑)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} represents yin {{ill|Earth|ja|土|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}, and they interact by {{ill|Mutual Generation|ja|五行思想#相生（そうじょう）|lt=Mutual Generation|lt_ja=相生|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} (Fire generates Earth).

