'''Yin Fire Ox also known as  Teichuu''' (丁丑) (ひのとうし、ていかのうし、ていちゅう) is one of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|干支|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sexagenary cycle|qq=}}.

It is the 14th combination in the Sexagenary cycle; the preceding combination is {{ill|Bingzi|ja|1=Yang Fire Rat|2=ja|丙子|1=Yang Fire Rat|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bingzi|qq=}} and the following combination is {{ill|Wuyin|ja|戊寅|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wuyin|qq=}}. In the system of {{ill|Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|ja|陰陽五行思想|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|lt=Yin-Yang Five Elements|lt_ja=陰陽五行|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|qq=}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|lt=Ten Heavenly Stems|ja|十干|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Heavenly Stems|qq=}}’ {{ill|Ding|ja|丁|1=Hinoto (丁)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ding|13=User:Immanuelle/Hinoto (丁)|qq=}} represents yin {{ill|Fire|ja|火|1=Fire (wuxing)|lt=Fire (火)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fire|qq=}}, while the {{ill|Twelve Earthly Branches|1=Earthly Branches|lt=Twelve Earthly Branches|ja|十二支|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Twelve Earthly Branches|13=User:Immanuelle/Earthly Branches|qq=}}’ {{ill|Ox|ja|丑|1=Ox (zodiac)|lt=Ox (丑)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ox|13=User:Immanuelle/Ox (zodiac)|qq=}} represents yin {{ill|Earth|ja|土|1=Earth (wuxing)|lt=Earth (土)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Earth|qq=}}, and they interact by {{ill|Mutual Generation|ja|五行思想#相生（そうじょう）|lt=Mutual Generation|lt_ja=相生|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mutual Generation|qq=}} (Fire generates Earth).

