== Months of Teichuu ==
In a {{ill|Common Era|ja|西暦|1=Common Era|2=ja|3=西暦|4=zh|5=公元|6=es|7=Era común|8=nl|9=Gangbare jaartelling|10=simple|11=Common Era|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Common Era|13=User:Immanuelle/Common Era|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Common Era|13=User:Immanuelle/Common Era|qq=}} year whose final digit is 4 or 9 (i.e. when the Ten Heavenly Stems are {{ill|Jia|ja|甲|1=Kinoe (甲)|lt=Kinoe (甲)|2=ja|3=甲|4=zh|5=甲|1=Kinoe (甲)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jia|13=User:Immanuelle/Kinoe (甲)|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jia|13=User:Immanuelle/Kinoe (甲)|qq=}} or {{ill|Ji|ja|己|1=Tsuchinoto (己)|lt=Tsuchinoto (己)|2=ja|3=己|4=zh|5=己|1=Tsuchinoto (己)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ji|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsuchinoto (己)|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ji|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsuchinoto (己)|qq=}}), the month of {{ill|December|ja|12月|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/December|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/December|qq=}} becomes the {{ill|Month (Calendar)|ja|月 (暦)|lt=Month|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Month (Calendar)|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Month (Calendar)|qq=}} of Teichuu. However, the term “month” here may refer either to the month of the {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}} or to a seasonal month (from {{ill|Minor Cold|ja|小寒|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Minor Cold|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Minor Cold|qq=}} until the day before {{ill|Beginning of Spring|ja|立春|1=Lichun|lt=Risshun|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Beginning of Spring|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Beginning of Spring|13=User:Immanuelle/Lichun|qq=}}) as applicable.

